		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Payment gateway</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>A <b>payment gateway</b> is an <a href="/wiki/E-commerce" title="E-commerce" class="mw-redirect">e-commerce</a> <a href="/wiki/Application_service_provider" title="Application service provider">application service provider</a> service that authorizes payments for <a href="/wiki/Ebusiness" title="Ebusiness" class="mw-redirect">e-businesses</a>, <a href="/wiki/E-tailer" title="E-tailer">online retailers</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bricks_and_clicks_business_model" title="Bricks and clicks business model" class="mw-redirect">bricks and clicks</a>, or traditional <a href="/wiki/Brick_and_mortar" title="Brick and mortar" class="mw-redirect">brick and mortar</a>. It is the equivalent of a physical <a href="/wiki/Point_of_sale" title="Point of sale">point of sale</a> terminal located in most retail outlets. Payment <a href="/wiki/Gateway#Computer_Terminology" title="Gateway">gateway</a> protects credit cards details encrypting sensitive information, such as <a href="/wiki/Credit_card" title="Credit card">credit card</a> numbers, to ensure that information passes securely between the customer and the merchant and also between merchant and <a href="/wiki/Payment_processor" title="Payment processor">payment processor</a>.</p>
